                  <div class="blog-title1">
                    <h2>Active and Passive Voice Worksheets</h2>
                  </div>

                  <div class="clearfix"></div>
    
                  <div class="pt30">
                    <div class="row">
                      <div class="pedagogy-content-element">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 blog-text-top">
                          <h4 class="title desc-title">What is Active and Passive Voice?</h4>
                            <div class="">
                              <p>Active voice means that a sentence has a subject that acts upon its verb. Passive voice means that a subject is a recipient of a verb's action.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>      
                      </div>
                      
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="pt30">
                    <div class="row">
                      <div class="pedagogy-content-element">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 blog-text-top">
                          <h4 class="title desc-title">How are Active and Passive Voice Worksheets designed?</h4>
                            <div class="">
                              <p>The worksheets will include questions for students to identify what is active voice and what is passive voice. Students will also solve questions on converting sentences from one voice to another. They will also learn how to convert the sentences in various tenses using easy-to-remember formulae.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>      
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="pt30">
                    <div class="row">
                      <div class="pedagogy-content-element">
                        <div class="col-lg-12 blog-text-top">
                          <h4 class="title desc-title">What are the benefits of solving Active and Passive Voice Worksheets?</h4>
                            <div class="">
                              <p>These worksheets subject students to several different types of questions which help them to get enough practice of the topic. Thus, they inevitably get good grades while having crystal clear concepts. Most real world conversations employ the use of active and passive voice. Hence, students feel comfortable to use it in their speech themselves, making them confident speakers. The use of these techniques make us the best online grammar classes for kids.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>      
                      </div>
                    </div>
